The hook `hh` from class `Base2` overrides the post-setup hook from class `Base`. However, class `Base` also decorates `hh` as a post-compile hook, and this leaks into `Derived`, which calls `hh` (inherited from `Base2`) both as a post-setup and post-compile hooks. `hh` here should only be called as a post-setup hook.

Users should get an error when this is attempted. Otherwise the code below would be legal (and it probably shouldn't!)
```python
@rfm.simple_test
class MyTest(rfm.RunOnlyRegressionTest):
    ...
    my_attr = required

    @run_after('init')
    def my_hook(self):
        print(self.my_attr) # This would print the reframe.core.variables._UndefinedType object.
```

